**Issue :** 

The fetch-releases.js script iterates through all repositories in the CSV to find new job postings. For a large list, this will quickly trigger GitHub's secondary rate limits if an authenticated GH_TOKEN is not used or if requests aren't staggered.
Improvement: Add an optional token header to the fetch requests and implement a small delay (e.g., 200ms) between repository checks in the loop.

**File Path :** `open-source-jobs/scripts/fetch-releases.js`

**Code Idea :**

```
const headers = process.env.GH_TOKEN ? { Authorization: `token ${process.env.GH_TOKEN}` } : {};
// Inside the loop:
await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 200));
```

**Issue :** 

When users share a specific job update or the homepage on social media, there is no dynamic OpenGraph preview. The project has an og-image.svg, but it is not dynamically populated with job data.
Improvement: Implement dynamic metadata in the Next.js layout.tsx or individual page components to improve social sharing visibility.

**File Path** :  `open-source-jobs/app/layout.tsx`

**Code logic :**

```
export const metadata = {
  title: 'Open Source Jobs',
  description: 'Find jobs at companies building open source software.',
  openGraph: {
    images: ['/og-image.svg'],
  },
};
```
